Solution 1:
Substituting u=\cos x, \dee{u}=-\sin x\,\dee{x}, \sin^2 x= 1-\cos^2x=1-u^2,
gives


\int \tan^3 x \sec^5x \,\dee{x}
&=\int\frac{\sin^3 x}{\cos^8 x}\,\dee{x}
